The paper discusses transformations of deep neural networks, specifically rectifier networks and residual networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also discusses the advantages of deep neural networks over shallow neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions computer vision tasks, which suggests the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the representation of functions, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions natural language processing tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
